gw.api.productedition

Class DatabaseProductEdition

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.productedition.DatabaseProductEdition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProductEdition

    public class DatabaseProductEdition
extends java.lang.Object
implements ProductEdition
    Represents a product edition with all of its rules. For now this only handles APD existence rules for product model objects.

    The ProductEdition interface has separate methods for dealing with existence and availability. However existence and availability are treated as one concept in APD, with one type of rule. This class maps the APD rule result into an existence or availability result as needed.

    • Constructor Detail

      • DatabaseProductEdition

        public DatabaseProductEdition(InstalledEdition edition,
                              DatabaseProductEdition previousEdition)
        Creates a new product edition from an InstalledEdition and a previous product edition. The new edition will include all the rules from the previous edition, as well as all the rules from the InstalledEdition (which may overwrite the previous rules). The intention is for product editions to be created in order by their effective date, with each edition being passed in to create the next edition.
